&lt;p>Landauer, Rolf. &amp;ldquo;Inadequacy of entropy and entropy derivatives in characterizing the steady state.&amp;rdquo; &lt;em>Physical Review A&lt;/em> 12.2 (1975): 636.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Introduction</title><link>/docs/guides/markov-chain-theory/introduction/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/guides/markov-chain-theory/introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p>This guide explores the Markov chain theory of rattling developed in &lt;a href="/references/calvertrandall/">Calvert–Randall (2024)&lt;/a>. It assumes only basic knowledge of finite Markov chains, like the jump-hold description of continuous-time Markov chains and the major theorems about the existence and uniqueness of stationary distributions.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Rattling</title><link>/docs/background/rattling/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/background/rattling/</guid><description>&lt;p>Guides lead a user through a specific task they want to accomplish, often with a sequence of steps. Writing a good guide requires thinking about what your users are trying to do.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Vicsek model via Rattling</title><link>/docs/background/vicsek-model-via-rattling/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/background/vicsek-model-via-rattling/</guid><description/></item><item><title>For life scientists</title><link>/tutorials/tutorial-for-life-scientists/</link><pubDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2024 01:33:27 -0600</pubDate><guid>/tutorials/tutorial-for-life-scientists/</guid><description/></item><item><title>For engineers</title><link>/tutorials/tutorial-for-engineers/</link><pubDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2024 01:33:27 -0600</pubDate><guid>/tutorials/tutorial-for-engineers/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Announcement</title><link>/blog/announcement/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/blog/announcement/</guid><description>&lt;p>Pavel a